What if we just drop the > greenposting and write actual prose.
Ironically, it might be better for shorts than something like Happiest Place on Fur, because in shorts you need to convey as much meaning as possible, and with greenposting any structural tricks are pretty much limited to short decisive lines. I'm not a writer but maybe actual prose could help convey little meanings for instance it could make foreshadowing easier. With greenposting foreshadowing sticks out like a white crow.
